70305c87-0456-454b-93db-f7612b7b390d	Just trying to switch from VS Code to neovim, liking it to be honest.	So, I've heard a lot about vi, vim, neovim. Neovim is the newest, best and fastest of all vi editors. I'll be using neovim. Vi is the oldest, vim is vi improved, and neovim is vim improved with a lot of upgraded features and better defaults. Basically you don't have to use your mouse ever once u open vim editor. It's around 15mb with pretty loaded features. Nice and easy shortcuts for everything required in a text editor, like pressing dd in command mode deletes whole line, :w saves the file, :q quits, :colorscheme <theme_name> changes color scheme, :Ex for inbuilt file explorer, and a lot of plugins available for everything to make it a fully fledged IDE, like autocompletion, syntax correction, extensions, etc. Even after 15-20 plugins installed it took around 70-80mb of ram (vscode takes 300-400mb without any extension, cuz it uses electron).\nso yeah let's see how far I go with this, if I make this as my habit, and there's no going back for me.\n\nEdit(25th July): So after using vim/neovim for more than four months as a Linux user, I can say it's in my habit. I mean I can edit, navigate, save, update, etc, a file. But practically, terminal editors like vim/neovim or nano are only better for single file creation, editing, updating, etc. Like it's a complete replacement for Notepad for me. But it becomes complex when you try to use it as more than a text editor, e.g. for coding. Editing multiple files simultaneously, built in LSP, ESLint and terminal, preview of Markdown, Vast extensions makes me use VS Code (or VSCodium, an open source fork of vs code with removed Telemetry and Microsoft branding) over vim for programming. Vim is really nice when i can just open an existing file or create one with `nvim README.md`, and write whatever I want,  then save it, done. For more than just text editing, VS Code/(Codium) wins, and I love using it a lot in Linux compared to Windows. I'll be using both for their specific purpose.	f	2025-03-13 02:36:23.096+00	2025-07-25 06:57:13.537+00	61e5569a-8633-40f1-8f4f-8b2e60c8c036
