b2bed835-316d-4a59-a2cb-2decfd5fffa6	Open source alternatives	Here I'm just gonna provide best open source tools for specific purposes:\n1. Browser: Vivaldi, Brave, Ungoogled Chromium, Firefox, LibreWolf, Tor, Helium\n2. Github/Gitlab/Bitbucket alternative: Gitea (self hosted)\n3. Audio/Video player: VLC, SMPlayer\n4. Operating system: Linux distros (Linux Mint, Ubuntu, Fedora, Debian)\n5. Postman Alternative: Hoppscotch\n5. Firebase alternative: Supabase\n6. MS Office Alternative: Libreoffice, Openoffice\n7. Whatsapp Alternative: Signal, Session or SimpleX (no email/number), Ricochet Refresh (dark net + no email/number)\n8. Tailscale alternative: Headscale (self hosted)\n9. Youtube alternative: Revanced Youtube, NewPipe\n10. Spotify alternative: Spotube, DAB music player\n11. Code/text editor: Neovim, VS Code\n12. Bootable USB: Rufus or Balenaetcher (flashing), Ventoy (more than one ISO in one pendrive)\n\nI'll keep updating this list	f	2025-04-14 17:11:11.966+00	2026-01-23 07:04:05.35+00	61e5569a-8633-40f1-8f4f-8b2e60c8c036
