cef83c8b-aa1e-45cf-bf4f-596e31ac053d	Switched to Linux Mint from Ubuntu, corrupted windows while doing so lol	Linux Mint Cinnamon is a better and less bloated version of ubuntu. I deleted Ubuntu's 50 gb partition, and restarted pc, and it was a mistake. Pc didn't boot, it showed a "grub rescue" command line, and there was no way i could get into windows. I also had formatted the bootable pendrive to store personal files (later I got to know about ventoy, where we could have more than one iso files, along with personal files in one bootable USB,).  I used someone else's laptop to create a windows bootable USB. I installed windows first, then I installed Linux Mint on that 50 gb partition. Typing from Linux mint right now. I was just having some low fps in full screen games. I fixed that by going to settings > preferences > general > Disable compositing for full screen windows and i can game on it too.\n\nEdit (24 Apr): I've switched from Cinnamon edition to Mate edition, it's much lighter, and still better looking than xcfe, this was Mint's default edition before cinnamon, it's based on Gnome 2. It's also running games faster, i just had to disable composition in Control Centre -> Look and Feel --> Windows --> Compositing manager\n\nEdit (25 Apr): Trying the XFCE edition. So xfce runs smooth, has more features than mate, and for gaming, in desktop settings, i selected the windows manager as "xfwm4 + compton", and turned off composition in windows tweaks. Now it's running perfect, and takes less ram too. \n\nConclusion: All three desktops are good for their use cases.\n\nEdit (12 May): Later I tried many other distros like Lubuntu, Xubuntu, Zorin OS, and all distros were perfect in their own way. Now if I wanna try any linux distro, Instead of downloading the ISO image, I can just visit distrosea website or download the iso and move it to ventoy pendrive.\n\nEdit (30 May): Also tried Fedora, and I can say that after Linux Mint and Ubuntu, it's my most favorite. It's just plain simple linux system, as vanilla as possible. Plus I love KDE distros like Fedora kde and Kubuntu as same as Mint. I'm planning to switch between them regularly. XFCE is also preferred if I'm craving speed without losing much eye-candy. It's simple and fast.\n\nEdit (6 Sep): Sticking with Arch based distros. Endeavour OS and Cachy OS are the best ones. Sticking with Cachy OS as it's kernel is much more faster.	f	2025-03-20 14:50:59.728+00	2025-09-06 10:33:10.119+00	61e5569a-8633-40f1-8f4f-8b2e60c8c036
9bbabd42-9d45-4d2d-8802-ea7e1654decc	Planning to improve the UI and add profile viewing	So I haven't changed the UI since I developed The Blog Zone except the site was in light mode initially then I converted it to dark mode. But I feel like it's time and since my college exams are finished, I'm bored. I'll use shadcn and let's see how the new UI looks. I'll also be adding theme toggle since the site only has dark mode right now. I'll keep the old one for backup. Also I'll be adding profile viewing. Right now you can only view your profile and can change credentials. I'll be adding profile with posts and comments done by user both for current user and while viewing other users too.\n\nEdit: Updated it!	f	2025-12-27 08:56:12.394+00	2025-12-27 12:19:35.822+00	61e5569a-8633-40f1-8f4f-8b2e60c8c036
