39d45ba5-7c1e-4298-a7a2-f4f8818fc789	Major Update: Encryption in private posts	Previously all private posts were being saved in database in original plain text, and anyone with the database access (including me) could see those posts. Now I've added the feature to encrypt the private posts first and save them to database. Now for decryption it'll first check if it's the author of the post trying to access the blog. If yes it decrypts the post (using crypto module with encryption key stored securely in .env),  otherwise it'll throw an error. I also had to delete all private posts, because they weren't encrypted and hence there was error when fetching the private posts. But I have kept a copy of all private posts, and gave it to my friends.\n\nNow obviously if I'm the only who's adding encryption method to the data, then i can decrypt them too but with "some" hardwork, and I'm too lazy for that.\nWhen creating/editing post, you'll see a link where you can learn about this more.	f	2025-04-29 15:54:17.428+00	2026-01-02 11:47:18.747+00	61e5569a-8633-40f1-8f4f-8b2e60c8c036
