d5265da6-f704-4857-8026-f417ff92523e	AI vs Humans: Who Really Writes Better Code?	In the last few years, AI-powered code generation has gone from science fiction to daily reality. Tools like GitHub Copilot and ChatGPT now help millions of developers write code faster but does that mean humans are being replaced? Not quite.\n\nHere’s the interesting part: studies show that developers using AI coding assistants can complete tasks 30–55% faster than those coding alone. In one GitHub survey, 88% of developers said AI helped them feel more productive, and 74% said it helped them learn new coding techniques. That’s a big win for speed and education.\n\nHowever, humans still dominate where it matters most. AI can generate code, but it often lacks context awareness, business logic understanding, and long-term architectural thinking. Research has found that up to 40% of AI-generated code may contain bugs or security issues if not reviewed carefully. Humans excel at creativity, ethical judgment, and understanding user needs areas where AI still struggles.\n\nThe real future isn’t AI vs humans. It’s AI + humans. AI handles repetitive tasks, boilerplate code, and quick suggestions, while humans focus on design, problem-solving, and innovation. Think of AI as a super-fast junior developer and humans as the experienced architects guiding the build.\n\nIn coding, teamwork wins. 🚀	f	2026-01-23 06:56:54.874+00	2026-01-23 06:56:54.875+00	547a7e5d-cacb-47af-848b-72c73032acde
